
	OAR site README

Requirements :
	- ruby
	- webgen (A template based static website generator)
	- bibtex, bibtex2html
	- python-docutils (rst format)

To generate and updade site
	- make html 
	- make update SITE=intra-id.imag.fr:/www-id/id/Logiciels/OAR/ or
	scp -r output/* intra-id.imag.fr:/www-id/id/Logiciels/OAR/


To add page
	- For example see index.page in scr directory.
	- Header controls page's position in site and format.
		- It's encompass by --- delemiters (it's in yaml format)
		- 
	- By default page use the Textile simple markup language (see http://hobix.com/textile/quick.html).
	

To update news
	- update index.page (3 headlines suggested)
	- update news.page (full length)
	- repect format (table, spanrow (\2),  top vertical-align (^) in Textile format )


Directory Contents
-src: 		pages and images
-rst-oar-doc: 	doc in rst format and script to produce html
-bib:		bibtex of article (integrate by a plugin via bibliotex tag)
-plugin:	plugin for bibtex


